 demimonde. Kafū's place in Japan's intellectual history and his influence on other writers are also discussed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, Western, in literature. 0aEast and West in literature. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438439082423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438439082/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles